## Interpretation Notes

- Quality is assertion pass rate, falling back to case pass rate when a case has no assertions.
- Reliability is request success rate before quality assertions.
- Performance is scored against `run.performance_targets.p95_latency_seconds`.
- Cost is normalized so the cheapest nonzero provider receives 100.
- Model authenticity probes are high-confidence mismatch detectors, not cryptographic proof of model identity.
- Transport security should be checked with `llm-gateway-eval audit --online-tls` before production use.
- Dynamic canary and tamper probes detect suspicious behavior; they cannot prove a gateway never modifies prompts.
- Operations is a neutral MVP placeholder until audit, RBAC, rollout, and support evidence are collected.
